Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.02,0:00:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome, brothers and sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.99,0:00:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In this month’s program,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.32,0:00:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll review who the May 2020 Wa{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}tchtower
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.33,0:00:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,identified as “the king of the north,”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.33,0:00:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll learn how knowing this
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.00,0:00:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,affects each one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.07,0:00:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll also see\Nhow perseverance helps us
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.50,0:00:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,reach our spiritual goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.94,0:00:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ll debut an exciting new series
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.34,0:00:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,made especially for teenagers.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.28,0:00:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This is JW Broadcasting for May 2021.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.81,0:01:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,My theme is “‘The King of the North’\Nin the Time of the End.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.55,0:01:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In recent years, the Russian government
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.68,0:01:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,has persecuted our brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.32,0:01:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,who live in that country.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.32,0:01:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve heard reports\Nabout the police invading Kingdom Halls
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.09,0:01:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and breaking up meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.39,0:01:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The government has labeled\NJehovah’s Witnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.43,0:01:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,as an “extremist group.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.57,0:01:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It has seized our properties\Nand imprisoned our brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.14,0:01:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Please watch a brief video
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.24,0:01:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that reviews some of the trials
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.27,0:01:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s people in Russia have faced.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.18,0:01:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,On April 20, 2017,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.55,0:01:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the Supreme Court\Nof the Russian Federation criminalized
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.79,0:01:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the activity of Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.96,0:01:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,As of July 4, 2019,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.59,0:01:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,authorities have progressively\Nseized 131 of the properties
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.46,0:01:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,owned by Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.07,0:01:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,with an additional 60 properties\Nsubject to confiscation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.70,0:02:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the seized properties
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.74,0:02:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,was the former\NRussia branch complex in Solnechnoye.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.44,0:02:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time of filming,\Nthe Russian authorities continue
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.11,0:02:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,their aggressive attack\Non Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.21,0:02:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,As of August 17, 2020,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.05,0:02:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,there were 42 Witnesses\Nwho were in pretrial detention
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.89,0:02:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,or sentenced to prison,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.32,0:02:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,32 who were under house arrest,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.39,0:02:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and 169 who were not allowed\Nto leave their hometown.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.70,0:02:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All have been charged with organizing,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.43,0:02:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,participating in, or financing the activity
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.07,0:02:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of a so-called “extremist” organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.77,0:02:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,At least 380 Witnesses were,\Nat the time, under investigation
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.81,0:02:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,—ranging in age from 19 to 89 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.71,0:02:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What has this meant\Nfor the individuals affected?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.55,0:02:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,As an example,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.15,0:02:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,on June 3, 2018,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.52,0:02:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Sergey Klimov was arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.02,0:02:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Local authorities initiated
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.99,0:02:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,criminal charges against him,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.83,0:03:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,placing him\Nin pretrial detention for two months.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.83,0:03:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This detention was extended seven times,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.07,0:03:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,separating him from his wife and family
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.14,0:03:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,for a year and five months,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.30,0:03:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,before he was finally tried and sentenced.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.11,0:03:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,On November 5, 2019,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.11,0:03:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,he was sentenced to six years in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.05,0:03:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Two of our dear young people in Russia,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.19,0:03:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Yegor Baranov\Nand Sister Darya Dulova,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.26,0:03:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,are courageously facing criminal conviction
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.56,0:03:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and potential long-term imprisonment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.20,0:03:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Baranov is only 19 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.97,0:03:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When the authorities raided her home,\NSister Dulova was only 18 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.11,0:03:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,By means of the Newsroom on jw.org,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.31,0:03:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we are informed of updated news events.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.64,0:03:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This page includes links to name lists
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.65,0:03:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of Witnesses\Ncurrently imprisoned for their faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.32,0:03:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,which can help us include\Nthem specifically in our prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.49,0:03:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers and sisters in Russia\Nare resolved to remain loyal to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.82,0:04:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,despite any opposition,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.49,0:04:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and they put their confidence\Nin him in the assurance
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.09,0:04:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah is on their side!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.28,0:04:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It shouldn’t surprise us
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.28,0:04:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that this powerful government\Nhas been persecuting
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.58,0:04:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,our peaceful,\Nlaw-abiding brothers and sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.59,0:04:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.32,0:04:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that government\Nis fulfilling Bible prophecy!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.23,0:04:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Please find Daniel chapter 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.33,0:04:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In verse 40, it refers\Nto what the Bible calls
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.23,0:04:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“the king of the north.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.24,0:04:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Of that “king,” Daniel 11:41 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.51,0:04:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“He will also enter\Ninto the land of the Decoration,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.45,0:05:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and many lands will be made to stumble.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.45,0:05:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, Russia and its allies
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.49,0:05:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,are filling the role\Nof the king of the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.09,0:05:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel foretold that this king would enter
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.29,0:05:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“the land of the Decoration,”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.33,0:05:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning that he would interfere\Nin a significant way
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.03,0:05:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,with the activities of God’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.20,0:05:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,As discussed in the May 2020 {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Watchtower,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.81,0:05:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Russia and its allies\Nare not the first political power
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.38,0:05:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to act as the king of the north,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.75,0:05:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but they may well be the last.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.62,0:05:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In this program, we will do three things:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.02,0:05:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,First,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.95,0:05:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll briefly trace\Nthe fulfillment of the prophecy
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.56,0:05:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,recorded in Daniel chapter 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.03,0:05:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, we’ll look at how that prophecy
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.46,0:05:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is being fulfilled today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.03,0:05:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And third, we’ll discuss\Nhow knowing this information
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.04,0:05:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,should affect the decisions that we make.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.51,0:06:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Herman van Selm,\Na helper to the Writing Committee,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.45,0:06:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,will help us review\Nsome of the key points of the prophecy
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.52,0:06:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,recorded in Daniel chapter 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.39,0:06:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Herman,\Nfor helping me with this presentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.06,0:06:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a pleasure to be with you, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.79,0:06:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for inviting me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.23,0:06:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,First, let’s briefly trace
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.67,0:06:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,how the prophecy has been fulfilled so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.17,0:06:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The prophecy in Daniel chapter 11 mentions
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.77,0:06:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“the king of the north”\Nand “the king of the south.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.61,0:06:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, why are they described like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.21,0:06:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, initially,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.21,0:06:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,these powers were located north and south
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.35,0:06:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of the literal land of Israel,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.72,0:06:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,thus the names king of the north
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.02,0:06:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and king of the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.46,0:06:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,These powers could be viewed as two thrones.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.40,0:06:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Over time, those thrones have been occupied
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.26,0:06:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,by various political powers
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.27,0:07:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and these rival kings compete\Nfor world domination.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.57,0:07:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And what about Jehovah’s people?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.97,0:07:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They are right at the center\Nof this conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.31,0:07:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But let’s start at the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.38,0:07:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ken,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.32,0:07:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the origin\Nof the kings of the north and of the south?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.79,0:07:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The kings of the north and of the south
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.36,0:07:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,both rose from the empire
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.59,0:07:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,established by Alexander the Great.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.70,0:07:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,One line of kings ruled over Egypt,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.13,0:07:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,which is south of Israel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.27,0:07:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And that dynasty was the first
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.77,0:07:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to fill the role of king of the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.34,0:07:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,During this period, another line of kings
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.98,0:07:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,ruled an area north of Israel
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.85,0:07:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and those kings filled the role
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.08,0:07:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of king of the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.08,0:07:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the Roman Empire took over
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.45,0:07:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as king of the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.86,0:07:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,As discussed in the May 2020 {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Watchtower,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.09,0:07:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s people are the focal point
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.43,0:08:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of the prophecy\Nrecorded in Daniel chapter 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.80,0:08:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The angel who spoke with Daniel\Nsaid that the prophecy
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.14,0:08:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,would help him\N“understand what will befall your people”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.01,0:08:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,—that is, the nation of Israel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.81,0:08:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And what, in fact, happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.18,0:08:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the Jewish nation\Nwas God’s people until 33 C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.15,0:08:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But after that, a change occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.66,0:08:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah poured out his holy spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.26,0:08:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,on Christ’s followers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.59,0:08:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And from then on,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.26,0:08:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the congregation of true Christians
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.66,0:08:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,became God’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.40,0:08:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Galatians 6:16 refers to them
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.54,0:08:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,as “the Israel of God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.27,0:08:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That point is significant
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.88,0:08:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because the kings of the north and south\Ncan only be identified
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.35,0:08:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,when there is a clearly defined group\Nof God’s people on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.29,0:08:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.66,0:09:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Because, as we just considered,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.06,0:09:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the angel had told Daniel
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.16,0:09:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that the prophecy centers on God’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.56,0:09:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In the second century C.E.,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.37,0:09:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,true Christians were overgrown
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.30,0:09:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,by weedlike false Christians.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.27,0:09:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In his illustration\Nof the wheat and the weeds,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.81,0:09:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus foretold that this would happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.85,0:09:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That illustration is recorded
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.85,0:09:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,at Matthew 13:36-43.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.42,0:09:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So from the second century onward,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.06,0:09:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we can no longer identify\Nan organized group of true Christians.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.26,0:09:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And, as we considered, for that same reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.26,0:09:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,we also cannot identify
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.50,0:09:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the king of the north\Nand the king of the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.57,0:09:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the 1870’s, a group of Bible students
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.07,0:09:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,began to separate itself\Nfrom false Christians.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.48,0:09:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This group,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.74,0:09:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,which included Charles T. Russell,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.15,0:09:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,rejected teachings
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.78,0:10:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that were not based on the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.28,0:10:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And like the first-century Christians,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.95,0:10:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,they promoted the truths
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.96,0:10:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,taught in God’s Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.99,0:10:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this group underwent a development
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.43,0:10:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that is foretold at Malachi 3:1.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.83,0:10:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They were the “messenger”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.13,0:10:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,who would “clear up a way” before Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.97,0:10:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And as events that followed prove,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.91,0:10:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,this group clearly had God’s backing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.04,0:10:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So from the 1870’s onward,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.65,0:10:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,when true Christians began\Nto organize themselves as a group,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.92,0:10:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,we can again identify the political powers
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.12,0:10:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that fill the roles of the king of the north
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.32,0:10:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and king of the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.53,0:10:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time in history,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.63,0:10:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Britain was the dominant political force
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.93,0:10:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and it filled the role
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.50,0:10:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of the king of the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.74,0:10:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazingly, it was also in the 1870’s
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.81,0:11:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that the German Empire emerged
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.18,0:11:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and soon began to challenge Britain
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.48,0:11:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,for world domination.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.51,0:11:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This political power now filled the role
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.78,0:11:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of the king of the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.92,0:11:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel 11:25, 26 indicate
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.59,0:11:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that the two kings would clash
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.13,0:11:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the king of the north\Nwould lose many soldiers in the battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.50,0:11:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is exactly what happened
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.27,0:11:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,during World War I.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.77,0:11:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was during that war
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.94,0:11:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that Britain and its close ally,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.67,0:11:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the United States,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.34,0:11:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,forged a special bond.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.91,0:11:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So from this point on,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.15,0:11:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,during these last days,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.95,0:11:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the Anglo-American power
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.22,0:11:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,has been the king of the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.89,0:11:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That brings us to our second point:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.29,0:11:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,How has Daniel chapter 11 been fulfilled
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.76,0:11:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,from that time onward
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.00,0:11:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,until recent times?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.20,0:11:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,During World War I,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.37,0:12:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the king of the north\Nand the king of the south
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.97,0:12:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,persecuted those of God’s people\Nwho refused to fight in the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.74,0:12:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The king of the south even threw into jail
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.58,0:12:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,those who were taking the lead\Nin the preaching work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.75,0:12:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But let’s take a closer look\Nat the king of the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.82,0:12:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Has the political power filling that role
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.49,0:12:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,changed during the last days?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.26,0:12:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And how has it treated God’s people?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.86,0:12:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The identity of the king of the north
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.13,0:12:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,has changed three times during the last days.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.90,0:12:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting in the 1870’s\Nthrough to the end of the second world war,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.67,0:12:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the German Empire
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.68,0:12:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,filled the role of the king of the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.85,0:12:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In the period leading up to\Nand including World War II,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.12,0:12:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it persecuted God’s people without mercy,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.92,0:12:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,imprisoning thousands of our brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.82,0:12:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and killing hundreds of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.76,0:13:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Who replaced the German Empire\Nas the king of the north?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.83,0:13:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s an important question, Herman.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.80,0:13:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,After World War II,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.40,0:13:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the Soviet Union took on that role.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.04,0:13:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It also attacked God’s people,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.51,0:13:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,imprisoning them or sending them into exile.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.51,0:13:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But, Ken, Daniel 11:34 says
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.68,0:13:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that they—that is, God’s people—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.72,0:13:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,would be “given a little help.”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.59,0:13:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the significance of that statement?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.36,0:13:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This passage points forward to the time
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.16,0:13:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,when the Soviet Union collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.03,0:13:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Although God’s people suffered terribly\Nunder that government,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.90,0:13:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,they were “given a little help.”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.74,0:13:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In what way?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.74,0:13:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,After the USSR collapsed,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.34,0:13:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s people there could worship freely\Nfor a number of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.78,0:13:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In time, though, Russia and its allies
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.98,0:13:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,took on the role of the king of the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.68,0:13:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And like the other powers\Nthat filled the role of king of the north,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.82,0:14:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,this government has continued to oppress\NGod’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.63,0:14:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s watch the following video
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.03,0:14:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that outlines what has happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.77,0:14:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel received a prophecy
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.77,0:14:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,about the coming of two rivals:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.77,0:14:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“the king of the north”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.64,0:14:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and “the king of the south.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.05,0:14:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,How has it been fulfilled?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.82,0:14:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In the late 1800’s, the German Empire
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.82,0:14:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,became the king of the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.86,0:14:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That government brought
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.33,0:14:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,its “power and . . . heart
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.63,0:14:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“against the king of the south
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.96,0:14:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,with a large army.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.53,0:14:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, its navy was
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.73,0:14:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the second largest on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.07,0:14:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Who became the king of the south?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.21,0:14:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The alliance between Britain
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.21,0:14:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.41,0:14:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He fought during World War I
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.42,0:15:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“with an exceedingly large
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.42,0:15:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and mighty army.”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.32,0:15:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He “swept away” and “humbled”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.72,0:15:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the king of the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.09,0:15:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But that was not the end
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.49,0:15:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of the king of the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.60,0:15:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He turned his attention to and then hurled
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.73,0:15:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“denunciations against the holy covenant.”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.34,0:15:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He removed “the constant feature”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.60,0:15:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,by limiting the freedom of God’s people
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.61,0:15:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to preach,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.41,0:15:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,imprisoning many,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.68,0:15:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and even killing hundreds
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.68,0:15:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of God’s anointed ones
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.91,0:15:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and their fellow workers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.02,0:15:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,After Germany was defeated in World War II,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.52,0:15:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the Soviet Union
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.56,0:15:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,became the king of the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.63,0:15:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It worked with the king of the south
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.63,0:15:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to “put in place the disgusting thing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.03,0:15:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that causes desolation”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.53,0:15:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,—the United Nations.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.21,0:16:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Beginning in the early 1900’s,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.81,0:16:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the Soviet government tried to eliminate
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.12,0:16:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,religion in the lands under its control,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.45,0:16:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,fulfilling the words
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.89,0:16:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that he would “show no regard
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.46,0:16:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,for the God of his fathers.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.66,0:16:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave glory, not to the God of heaven,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.56,0:16:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but “to the god of fortresses.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.47,0:16:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,As prophesied,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.07,0:16:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,he used this military might
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.91,0:16:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,against the king of the south
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.44,0:16:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,by engaging “with him in a pushing.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.01,0:16:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Anglo-America competed
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.08,0:16:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,with the Soviet Union
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.18,0:16:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,for world domination,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.15,0:16:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,fighting in and supporting wars
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.28,0:16:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and political struggles around the globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.29,0:16:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,After the Soviet Union collapsed in 1991,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.99,0:16:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it was unclear who would fill the role\Nof the king of the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.66,0:16:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,For a time, God’s people there
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.73,0:17:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,had been able to preach\Nand worship peacefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.64,0:17:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But in recent years, Russia and its allies
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.67,0:17:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,have pushed back at the king of the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.61,0:17:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Both kings have accused each other
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.61,0:17:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of destructive cyber and economic attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.65,0:17:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But the king of the north has not limited
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.05,0:17:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,his attacks to the king of the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.39,0:17:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,As foretold, he also entered
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.46,0:17:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“into the land of the Decoration”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.86,0:17:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,—our realm of spiritual activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.50,0:17:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, Russian authorities continue
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.57,0:17:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to attack true worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.54,0:17:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We expect such persecution,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.67,0:17:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but we also expect it to end.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.26,0:18:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Our King, Jesus Christ,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.40,0:18:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is more powerful than any human government.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.87,0:18:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon he will destroy\Nnot only the kings of the north and the south
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.34,0:18:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but all of his enemies,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.44,0:18:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and he will deliver God’s loyal people.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.01,0:18:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a powerful and touching video!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.55,0:18:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,How are our brothers and sisters coping\Nwith the current persecution?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.82,0:18:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.82,0:19:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And what you’re going to see\Nwill break your heart
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.92,0:19:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but also strengthen your faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.86,0:19:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,At 6:00 a.m.,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.86,0:19:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,my husband and I were woken up
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.87,0:19:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,by a loud bang on the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.20,0:19:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as my husband had opened the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.27,0:19:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,people burst in shouting,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.34,0:19:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“Everyone on the floor!”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.21,0:19:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw them taking my husband into the kitchen
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.88,0:19:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and heard them
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.45,0:19:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,very aggressively\Nordering him to do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.45,0:19:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I heard some noise, and I realized
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.85,0:19:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was being beaten.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.39,0:19:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband, Feliks, and I
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.55,0:19:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,were on our way back from the shopping mall
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.36,0:19:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to the car park.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.86,0:19:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,A jeep with tinted windows
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.29,0:19:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,blocked our path, and people
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.03,0:19:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,with weapons\Njumped out, shouting:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.16,0:19:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“On the ground!\NDon’t move!”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.23,0:19:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We were thrown against the vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.64,0:19:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Feliks was sent\Nto a pretrial detention facility,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.67,0:19:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,where he spent a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.81,0:19:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,From the very first bang on the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.01,0:20:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I began praying to Jehovah\Nfor wisdom, calmness,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.32,0:20:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and for holy spirit\Nso that I could make the right decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.19,0:20:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and act in the right way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.45,0:20:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the whole day, I was praying.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.62,0:20:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah answered all my prayers,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.59,0:20:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and I felt that he was close at my side.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.57,0:20:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Before each court hearing\Nwhen I was very afraid
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.20,0:20:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and felt overwhelmed by emotion\Nand couldn’t calm myself down,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.50,0:20:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,it was prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.87,0:20:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that helped me to settle down.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.24,0:20:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,When they took us for interrogation,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.95,0:20:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I started panicking and, at that moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.22,0:20:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that I needed\Nto meditate on something positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.19,0:20:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.22,0:20:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I need to sing our songs.’
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.22,0:20:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And just one song came into my mind:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.63,0:20:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“He Will Make You Strong.”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.63,0:20:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It really strengthened me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.36,0:20:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Those words\Nabout how Jehovah gave his Son for us
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.87,0:20:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,show he loves us and will never leave us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.87,0:20:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.91,0:21:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,pray and tell me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.24,0:21:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that they are praying for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.38,0:21:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives me the feeling that I am part
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.81,0:21:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,of a large family.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.52,0:21:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,After the interrogation,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.09,0:21:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,he was sent home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.82,0:21:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband and I
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.76,0:21:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,continue to stick to our spiritual routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.43,0:21:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We continue to conduct family worship,\Nand we are always in the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.27,0:21:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers and sisters\Nconstantly support us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.84,0:21:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They write kind words;
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.44,0:21:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,they commend us;
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.41,0:21:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,they send us\Nencouraging scriptures from the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.31,0:21:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,In September 2019, Feliks was found guilty
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.95,0:21:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and sentenced to three years\Nin a general regime colony.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.99,0:21:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,When he and the other brothers arrived there,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.92,0:21:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,they were beaten up by officers\Nfrom the colony.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.33,0:21:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Feliks told me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.66,0:21:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that he prayed\Nwhile he was being beaten,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.27,0:22:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and he noticed that at that moment,\Nhe stopped feeling the pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.38,0:22:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,While he is behind bars,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.44,0:22:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Feliks tries to conduct\Nfamily worship with me by letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.25,0:22:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He picks certain themes\Nand some specific questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.12,0:22:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I do research
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.19,0:22:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in the publications\Nand send back what I find.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.46,0:22:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The scripture at Isaiah chapter 30\Nreally strengthens me,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.63,0:22:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,where it says that “your strength will be
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.93,0:22:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in keeping calm and showing trust.”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.34,0:22:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Although I tend to worry,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.74,0:22:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand that calmness is expressed
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.41,0:22:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,by fully trusting in Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.61,0:22:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I have become stronger\Nbecause thanks to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.75,0:22:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,in a way, I have developed almost a shell
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.49,0:22:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,against the difficulties
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.49,0:22:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that used to scare me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.52,0:22:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That confidence and faith help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.56,0:22:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah was with me,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.63,0:23:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and he will remain
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.16,0:23:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,close by me,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.50,0:23:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and we will be made stronger thanks to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.87,0:23:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and we will get through these trials.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.44,0:23:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we develop courage
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.28,0:23:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,like our brothers and sisters in Russia?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.45,0:23:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we must be convinced
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.71,0:23:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that the prophecies in the Bible\Nare trustworthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.22,0:23:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a topic discussed
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.25,0:23:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,by Brother David Splane of the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.06,0:23:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in the following Morning Worship program.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.63,0:23:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you’d just
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.06,0:23:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,take a look at today’s text,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.53,0:23:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it says: “Come and witness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.54,0:23:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the activities of Jehovah”—witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.64,0:23:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, according to a dictionary,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.64,0:23:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,a witness is someone\Nwho has personal knowledge of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.45,0:23:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can we be Witnesses of Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.65,0:24:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What personal knowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.36,0:24:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,do we have of his activities?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.53,0:24:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, first of all,\Nwe can testify to the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.43,0:24:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah can see into the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.73,0:24:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And when he does that,\Nhe is right 100 percent of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.50,0:24:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And second, we know that no one can prevent
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.44,0:24:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,what Jehovah foresees from coming true.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.24,0:24:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All of Jehovah’s prophecies come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.81,0:24:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, to illustrate the first point,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.32,0:24:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah can see into the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.52,0:24:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s consider two remarkable prophecies
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.99,0:24:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,concerning the destruction\Nof Jerusalem and its temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.99,0:24:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we know that\Nthrough the prophet Jeremiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.20,0:24:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah foretold\Nthat Jerusalem and the temple
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.00,0:24:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,would be destroyed by the Babylonians.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.20,0:24:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Did it come true?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.24,0:24:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely—in 607 B.C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.01,0:24:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah went further.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.14,0:24:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that Jerusalem would be rebuilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.85,0:25:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“They will rebuild the ancient ruins;
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.05,0:25:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“they will raise up\Nthe desolated places of the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.65,0:25:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and they will restore the devastated cities.”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.82,0:25:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And true worship would also be restored.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.36,0:25:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was quite a level of knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.46,0:25:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But there’s more.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.47,0:25:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah went further.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.50,0:25:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah also indicated
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.60,0:25:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that the spiritual revival wouldn’t last.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.51,0:25:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that is remarkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.74,0:25:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s implied by what we read\Nin the second part
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.58,0:25:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of Daniel 9:26.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.75,0:25:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d like you to have a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.85,0:25:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re going to be reading
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.75,0:25:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,two parts of this verse,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.09,0:25:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and it’s quite interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.09,0:25:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,—Daniel 9:26.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.66,0:25:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So now, what’s our objective here?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.47,0:25:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s to see that Jerusalem and its temple
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.24,0:26:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,would be destroyed a second time
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.51,0:26:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and that true worship would not last.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.68,0:26:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It says in the second part of verse 26:
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.48,0:26:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“And the people of a leader who is coming
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.25,0:26:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,will destroy the city and the holy place.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.99,0:26:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when these words were written,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.59,0:26:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerusalem and the temple\Nwere already in ruins.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.10,0:26:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah doesn’t say,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.20,0:26:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Nebuchadnezzar has destroyed\Nthe city and its temple.’
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.77,0:26:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He says:\N“The people of a leader who is coming.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.64,0:26:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The Roman general Titus in 70 C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.48,0:26:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“will destroy the city and the holy place.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.35,0:26:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In order for that prophecy to be fulfilled,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.62,0:26:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerusalem and the temple\Nwould have to be rebuilt
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.72,0:26:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and then destroyed a second time.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.36,0:26:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that is quite a level of knowledge\N—quite a level of information.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.16,0:26:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But what would make this necessary?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.90,0:27:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, when the Jews\Ncame back to the Promised Land
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.90,0:27:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and they were intent\Non restoring true worship,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.37,0:27:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,why would this fail?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.34,0:27:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And why would Jerusalem and the temple\Nbe destroyed a second time?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.28,0:27:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Part of it is due to what we find\Nin the first part of verse 26:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.42,0:27:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“Messiah will be cut off.”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.89,0:27:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jehovah foretold, foresaw,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.43,0:27:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that when the Messiah came,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.70,0:27:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the Jews would reject him.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.77,0:27:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He would be cut off.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.83,0:27:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And because of that, partly because of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.57,0:27:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerusalem and the temple would be destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.91,0:27:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,as it happens, in 70 C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.98,0:27:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, wait a minute, wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.78,0:27:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s think about that a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.98,0:27:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The Messiah comes first\Nand Jerusalem and the temple
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.35,0:27:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,are destroyed after that in 70 C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.89,0:27:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.96,0:28:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It means that the Messiah\Ncomes before 70 C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.73,0:28:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So we might ask our Jewish friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.13,0:28:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,why are you still waiting for the Messiah?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.37,0:28:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,70 C.E. has come and gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.54,0:28:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the Messiah came,\Nand he too proved to be a true prophet.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.54,0:28:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And a remarkable prophecy of Jesus\Nis found in the Sermon on the Mount.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.58,0:28:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s have a look at it and consider\Nthe implications of this prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.59,0:28:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Matthew chapter 7,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.56,0:28:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll read verses 22 and 23,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.63,0:28:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,an amazing prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.83,0:28:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, imagine: At this point, Jesus’ teachings
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.27,0:28:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,have not spread beyond Israel.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.34,0:28:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But notice verses 22 and 23:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.28,0:28:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“Many will say to me on that day:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.28,0:28:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Lord, Lord,\Ndid we not prophesy in your name,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.02,0:28:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and expel demons in your name,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.15,0:29:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“and perform many powerful works\Nin your name?’
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.12,0:29:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“And then I will declare to them:\N‘I never knew you!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.96,0:29:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Get away from me,\Nyou workers of lawlessness!’”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.33,0:29:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, isn’t that amazing?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.00,0:29:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If Jesus had simply predicted
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.87,0:29:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that his teachings would spread\Nthroughout the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.94,0:29:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you might say, “Well, there’s\Nnothing remarkable about that.”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.60,0:29:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jesus is saying something different.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.74,0:29:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus is foretelling
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.78,0:29:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,a great apostasy from his teachings.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.15,0:29:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus is foretelling the birth of Christendom
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.85,0:29:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,300 years before the event.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.02,0:29:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jesus foresees that many
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.03,0:29:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,are going to turn away from the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.16,0:29:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And by the end of the first century,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.10,0:29:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that apostasy was already at work, wasn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.13,0:29:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There were sects
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.07,0:29:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,—the sect of Nicolaus,\Nfor example, and other sects.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.44,0:29:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And now they’re on the cusp\Nof the great darkness,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.81,0:30:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the great apostasy, that’s going to set in\Nfrom the second century on.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.11,0:30:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And with this in mind, what does Jehovah do?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.85,0:30:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He makes an amazing statement
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.82,0:30:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,—Revelation 14—
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.63,0:30:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‘144,00 will be on Mount Zion with the Lamb.’
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.60,0:30:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There were nowhere near 144,000\Nin the truth in the first century.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.17,0:30:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And here Jehovah is saying\Nthere are going to be 144,000 in heaven
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.04,0:30:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,with the Lamb at the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.21,0:30:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But not only that, he goes further.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.31,0:30:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s going to be\Na ‘great crowd that no man can number.’
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.81,0:30:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,How could that ever come true?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.18,0:30:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Ours is the God of true prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.99,0:30:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.42,0:30:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the second point?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.66,0:30:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is that no one\Ncan prevent prophecy from being fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.66,0:30:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The Devil would love\Nto prevent that from taking place.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.77,0:30:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about Revelation 14.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.87,0:30:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If the Devil could make the number
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.60,0:30:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,one short of 144,000,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.37,0:31:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,he’d be happy because he would show
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.18,0:31:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah was inaccurate\Nin what he foretold.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.08,0:31:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that’s one\Nof the reasons why the Devil
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.12,0:31:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,has made war on the remnant\Nof the seed of the woman,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.82,0:31:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,if at all possible, to prevent that number
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.82,0:31:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of 144,000 from coming to pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.66,0:31:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But, of course, he’s going to fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.53,0:31:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And what about the prophecy in the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.07,0:31:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that America and Britain\Nwould become a dual world power?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.07,0:31:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Britain wouldn’t become a world power
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.54,0:31:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,at all if France\Nhad anything to say about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.88,0:31:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,France and Britain were sworn enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.95,0:31:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And for many, many, years,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.11,0:31:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,France was much richer\Nand much more powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.75,0:31:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,than Britain was.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.15,0:31:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally,\Nat the Battle of Waterloo in 1815,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.02,0:31:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,France had one last chance
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.96,0:31:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to prevent Britain\Nfrom becoming a world power.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.23,0:31:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And France should have won that battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.83,0:32:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything was stacked against the British.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.24,0:32:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But there was a driving rain,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.94,0:32:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a fatal miscalculation\Non the part of Napoleon,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.84,0:32:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and a few other factors\Nthat foiled their attempt.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.38,0:32:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And Britain did become a world power.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.62,0:32:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the end of the 19th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.18,0:32:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s quite true that the sun\Nnever set on the British Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.86,0:32:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, America and Britain\Nwere supposed to become a dual world power,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.29,0:32:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and Britain wasn’t the least bit interested\Nin sharing its power with America.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.97,0:32:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It tried to prevent America\Nfrom separating as a colony.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.97,0:32:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a long war,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.61,0:32:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and there were mistakes made on both sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.28,0:32:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But finally, America gained\Nits independence from Britain.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.91,0:32:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what do we find?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.31,0:32:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Some years after that,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.32,0:32:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Britain is sharing its power with America.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.25,0:32:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They are a dual world power.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.59,0:32:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Fighters against God will never prevail.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.63,0:33:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We serve “the God of true prophecy.”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.30,0:33:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And “what he foretells comes to be.”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.57,0:33:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,As we’ve discussed,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.57,0:33:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,each detail of the prophecy\Nrecorded at Daniel chapter 11
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.94,0:33:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,has come true so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.31,0:33:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We must have confidence
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.48,0:33:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that the remaining events\Ndescribed in that prophecy
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.75,0:33:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,will also come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.85,0:33:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We are living in the last days\Nof the time of the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.46,0:33:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, the nations will fulfill the prophecy
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.30,0:33:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Thessalonians 5:3:
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.17,0:33:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“Whenever it is that they are saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.90,0:33:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Peace and security!’
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.97,0:33:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“then sudden destruction\Nis to be instantly on them,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.28,0:33:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“just like birth pains on a pregnant woman,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.78,0:33:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and they will by no means escape.”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.75,0:33:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Then “sudden destruction”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.98,0:34:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,comes upon all parts of Satan’s system.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.66,0:34:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see on the screen,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.06,0:34:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel 12:1 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.73,0:34:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“During that time Michael will stand up,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.30,0:34:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“the great prince who is standing\Nin behalf of your people.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.37,0:34:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“And there will occur a time of distress\Nsuch as has not occurred
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.07,0:34:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“since there came to be a nation\Nuntil that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.71,0:34:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“And during that time\Nyour people will escape,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.18,0:34:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone who is found written down\Nin the book.”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.25,0:34:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That leads us into our third point:
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.56,0:34:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How should knowing the information
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.33,0:34:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have just discussed
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.06,0:34:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,affect the decisions that we make?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.83,0:34:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what we have reviewed\Nis not just interesting history;
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.80,0:34:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s a dramatic prelude
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.20,0:34:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to what will soon happen here on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.71,0:34:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has given his people this knowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.11,0:34:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we can act on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.11,0:35:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It should influence the choices we make.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.15,0:35:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following dramatization,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.32,0:35:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,notice how one young brother makes decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.12,0:35:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,based on his understanding\Nof Daniel’s prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.83,0:35:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That was my best friend, Lucas,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.07,0:35:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,when we were kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.73,0:35:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was me, Oscar.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.74,0:35:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We knew exactly what we wanted to do
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.11,0:35:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,when we grew up:
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.11,0:35:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Pioneer!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.61,0:35:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to Bethel!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.08,0:35:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Build Kingdom Halls!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.55,0:35:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We kept those goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.58,0:35:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And when graduation came,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.62,0:35:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,we were ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.56,0:35:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Our little business needed\Njust a few more accounts.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.23,0:35:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we’d have enough for us\Nand to help our families.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.20,0:35:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.24,0:35:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Day one of the service year
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.71,0:36:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,—and two new pioneers!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.55,0:36:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Where we live, . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.75,0:36:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don’t call me ever again!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.82,0:36:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . finding spiritual interest is tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.57,0:36:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We already have cleaners.\NThanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.24,0:36:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And finding enough work\Nwas harder than we thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.81,0:36:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,A few months in,\NI was sure
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.01,0:36:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah would help\Nif we just stuck it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.95,0:36:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Oscar.\NCan’t make it today.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.31,0:36:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Something came up.\NLucas.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.12,0:36:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What came up\Nwas an opportunity for more money,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.69,0:36:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but at what cost?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.50,0:36:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you quitting, or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.17,0:37:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I’m not quitting.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.67,0:37:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Pioneering or our business?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.04,0:37:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither, but you know the struggle here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.81,0:37:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Most brothers can afford\Nto pioneer for a year, two tops.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.45,0:37:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, it’s not full-time while I’m training.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.52,0:37:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a backup plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.05,0:37:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So Lucas stopped pioneering?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.56,0:38:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe he’s right.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.03,0:38:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s just being practical.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.10,0:38:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, is it wrong to quit\Nif you think it’s not working?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.44,0:38:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I struggled with the same question\Nwhen I pioneered.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.61,0:38:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever you decide,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.42,0:38:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,if you can tell Jehovah your reason
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.95,0:38:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,with a clean conscience,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.29,0:38:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,then it’s the right decision for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.03,0:38:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would I keep going\Nwhen it’s so difficult?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.77,0:38:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“Since all these things\Nare to be dissolved in this way,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.60,0:38:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“consider what sort of people\Nyou ought to be
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.07,0:38:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in holy acts of conduct\Nand deeds of godly devotion.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.59,0:39:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It really is “the last days,”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.83,0:39:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and people need “the good news.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.60,0:39:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And they’ll only hear it
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.60,0:39:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,if we keep up our “deeds of godly devotion”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.30,0:39:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,as best we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.34,0:39:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I prayed to endure and only stop pioneering
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.28,0:39:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,if my circumstances left no other choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.48,0:39:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And I prayed to see the blessings.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.33,0:39:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And after a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.36,0:39:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned that a little perseverance,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.20,0:39:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,with Jehovah’s spirit, can be contagious.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.21,0:40:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do you want to do\Nwhen you grow up?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.85,0:40:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Pioneer.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.18,0:40:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And go to Bethel?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.48,0:40:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.22,0:40:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And then maybe build Kingdom Halls.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.79,0:40:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You in?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.52,0:40:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.03,0:40:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That young brother was trying to figure out
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.60,0:40:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,what to do with his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.60,0:40:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He made a good decision\Nbecause he allowed Bible prophecy
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.57,0:40:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to influence his thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.68,0:40:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that teens everywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.14,0:40:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,face many challenges, and we feel for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.38,0:40:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I was once a teenager,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.12,0:40:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but I can’t even imagine\Nsome of the situations
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.25,0:40:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that you find yourselves in.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.49,0:40:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Governing Body loves you,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.06,0:40:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and we want to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.06,0:40:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So I’m very happy to announce a new series
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.40,0:40:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,—“My Teen Life.”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.47,0:40:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll hear from Witnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.67,0:40:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,who share the challenges\Nthey faced in their teens
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.87,0:41:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and how they overcame them\Nwith Jehovah’s help.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.21,0:41:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The interviews are candid;
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.24,0:41:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the issues are real.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.25,0:41:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s the first episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.36,0:41:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, when I was a teenager,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.93,0:41:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t see any benefit
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.53,0:41:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,in talking to my parents
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.93,0:41:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because they\Nliked different things than I liked.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.57,0:41:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought, ‘Well, what’s the point?’
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.64,0:41:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And I also wanted to be an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.07,0:41:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to feel like an adult\Nand be treated like an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.71,0:41:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember when my mom\Nused to pick me up from school.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.58,0:41:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,She wanted to show personal interest in me,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.98,0:41:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so she’d ask me:\N“Oh, how are your friends doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.15,0:41:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“How was school today?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.55,0:41:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a lot of homework?”
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.98,0:41:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But I just thought that she was being nosy.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.29,0:41:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I always had my earphones on.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.59,0:41:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And whenever my parents\Nwere trying to talk to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.23,0:41:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that was my chance\Nto just pop them in and ignore them.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.90,0:41:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The way my parents grew up wasn’t
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.10,0:42:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the same way that I grew up.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.47,0:42:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They grew up in a different country;
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.97,0:42:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,they spoke a different language;\Nthey grew up in a different time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.01,0:42:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,When you’re talking to somebody\Nwho doesn’t speak your language natively,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.08,0:42:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,oftentimes you won’t be able\Nto explain things from your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.11,0:42:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I had that challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.78,0:42:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn’t able to talk directly\Nto my parents heart to heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.15,0:42:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And so there was always this frustration
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.52,0:42:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in trying to really convey how I felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.26,0:42:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And I felt like I\Nwasn’t really getting through to my parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.10,0:42:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,When I went to my first pioneer school,\NI learned a lot about Jehovah’s qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.70,0:42:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of them was\Nhow he was a very approachable Person.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.64,0:42:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought to myself,\N‘Am I an approachable person?’
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.27,0:42:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought about how\NI acted in the ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.44,0:42:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and then at the meetings and then at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.98,0:42:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And I realized that at home\NI had a lot of things I needed to fix.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.48,0:42:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like it was two different worlds\NI was living in.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.99,0:42:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,One was when I was at school with my peers;
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.96,0:42:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like I was understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.06,0:43:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And at home,\NI kind of just withdrew to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.46,0:43:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn’t try to communicate with them\Nbecause it didn’t seem worth the effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.16,0:43:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried to figure out problems in my own way.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.23,0:43:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It was kind of trial and error.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.87,0:43:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I developed a lot of bad habits
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.08,0:43:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that today I’m still trying to overcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.85,0:43:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If I’d been able\Nto communicate with them more,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.75,0:43:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,if I’d been able to connect\Nwith them and ask for their help
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.82,0:43:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and get their support\Nand have them on my team,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.89,0:43:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,things would have gone a lot better.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.92,0:43:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And I really wish I had.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.26,0:43:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus, who was a perfect human being
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.69,0:43:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and who had perfect judgment,\Ndidn’t make decisions on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.36,0:43:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He always looked to his Father for guidance.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.87,0:43:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And that got me thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.27,0:43:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Well, if Jesus did that,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.70,0:43:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,‘there has to be something good
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.77,0:43:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in it for me too.’
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.04,0:43:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What really helped me was Colossians 4:6.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.24,0:43:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew I needed to speak\Nmore graciously in the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.01,0:43:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I realized\Nthat I was speaking very defensively
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.85,0:43:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and that I needed\Nto be more approachable to my parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.35,0:44:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,When I first tried to talk with them,\Nof course,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.19,0:44:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it was awkward and I didn’t want to talk\Nabout anything personal
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.39,0:44:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because I wasn’t used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.63,0:44:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought I could maybe\Nask them about themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.80,0:44:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,—ask them how their day was\Nor what they liked from the meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.43,0:44:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just tried to show more interest in them
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.64,0:44:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of focusing on myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.60,0:44:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think that’s what got
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.87,0:44:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the conversations going 
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.94,0:44:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and got me comfortable
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.94,0:44:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to really talk with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.24,0:44:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so focused on how my parents\Nweren’t understanding me
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.25,0:44:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that I wasn’t really trying\Nto understand them.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.32,0:44:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,When I thought about my parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.45,0:44:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought about how much work\Nit takes to be a parent.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.56,0:44:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,From when I was a baby, for many years,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.79,0:44:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,they were working day and night\Nto try to care for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.06,0:44:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They never demanded a thank you\Nor anything from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.07,0:44:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They were really self-sacrificing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.30,0:44:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And I imagined:\N‘If I had to work that much for somebody,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.77,0:44:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,‘how would I feel if they\Ndidn’t really say thank you?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.81,0:44:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Or how would I feel
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.58,0:45:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,‘if this person whom I worked so hard for
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.98,0:45:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,didn’t really view me as their friend?’
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.75,0:45:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Later on, as I got older and started
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.92,0:45:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that communication going with my parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.36,0:45:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that taking their advice\Nand really listening to their opinions
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.49,0:45:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and always letting them know
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.66,0:45:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,what I’m going to do\Nand where I’m going to go
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.50,0:45:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,was a mature thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.30,0:45:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Our heart oftentimes
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.94,0:45:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,takes the driver’s seat, and it directs us
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.81,0:45:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to where it thinks it should go.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.27,0:45:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And oftentimes it goes\Nin the wrong direction,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.61,0:45:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and we sometimes get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.31,0:45:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we look back and say,\N“I wish I hadn’t done that.”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.98,0:45:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And our parents have been there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.99,0:45:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What they’re trying to do\Nfor us now is to tell us,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.46,0:45:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“Don’t let your heart\Ntake the driver’s seat.”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.69,0:45:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If I could talk to my teenage self,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.23,0:45:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I would tell myself to see\Nmy mom and dad more like coaches, 
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.50,0:45:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because I used to think\Nthey were always trying to criticize me
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.47,0:45:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and point out my faults.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.84,0:45:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But, really, they’re just trying to help me,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.31,0:46:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and they want me to have a happy life.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.38,0:46:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I really wish I knew that as a teenager.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.01,0:46:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But I’m glad I learned that now.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.33,0:46:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We hope that you’ll enjoy and benefit
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.80,0:46:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,from future episodes of “My Teen Life.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.94,0:46:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This new series is another way
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.48,0:46:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the Governing Body prepares Jehovah’s people
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.35,0:46:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to cope with today’s challenges
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.91,0:46:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and to be ready for what’s coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.32,0:46:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Bible prophecy shows that in the near future,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.26,0:46:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the nations will turn\Non all false religions and wipe them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.26,0:46:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, they will launch\Na final attack on God’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.90,0:47:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And what a mistake that will be!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.10,0:47:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,As discussed in the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Pure Worship{\r} book,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.44,0:47:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will respond to that attack
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.31,0:47:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,by unleashing his rage on the nations.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.91,0:47:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,After the dust of Armageddon settles,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.71,0:47:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,those with the earthly hope can look forward
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.22,0:47:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to a thousand years\Nof genuine peace and security,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.69,0:47:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,working under the rule of God’s Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.19,0:47:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Before that time comes,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.69,0:47:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we will continue to face\Ntrials and opposition,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.03,0:47:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but we can endure.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.10,0:47:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We have many modern-day examples
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.74,0:47:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can imitate right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.20,0:47:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Those examples can help all of us
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.77,0:47:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to be prepared, to stand firm,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.94,0:47:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and to remain fully united in the faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.71,0:47:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This month’s original song
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.55,0:47:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,entitled “One United People”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.39,0:47:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,encourages us to do just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.08,0:48:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We watch the storm clouds gather.\NWe’ve seen the signs before.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.59,0:48:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The wind of persecution\NIs no stranger to our door.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.70,0:48:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We will face each test with courage,\NWith Jehovah standing near.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.85,0:49:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And ‘no weapon formed against us’\NWill give any cause for fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.73,0:49:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We are\None united people,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.04,0:49:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Though we come\Nfrom ev’ry land.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.21,0:49:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We are\Nstanding firm together,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.15,0:49:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,For Jehovah\Nmakes us stand,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.09,0:49:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,For Jehovah\Nmakes us stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.61,0:50:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We wait with calm assurance\NFor Jehovah, the Most High—
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.72,0:50:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of our salvation\NWhose love will never die.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.94,0:50:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He will never leave his people,\NAnd his spirit makes us strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.05,0:50:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No, our enemies won’t break us.\NTo Jehovah we belong!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.97,0:50:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We are\None united people,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.64,0:51:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Though we come\Nfrom ev’ry land.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.01,0:51:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We are\Nstanding firm together,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.98,0:51:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,For Jehovah\Nmakes us stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.33,0:51:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We stand firm together;\NUnafraid we face the crowd.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.93,0:51:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And these hearts that beat within us\NWe have given to our God.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.71,0:51:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We are\None united people,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.19,0:51:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Though we come\Nfrom ev’ry land.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.56,0:51:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We are\Nstanding firm together,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.50,0:52:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,For Jehovah\Nmakes us stand,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.07,0:52:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,For Jehovah\Nmakes us stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.96,0:52:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The stirring theme of this year’s convention
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.66,0:52:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is “Powerful By Faith!”
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.50,0:52:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We will learn what faith is,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.90,0:52:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,why it is essential,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.94,0:52:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and how we can acquire it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.27,0:52:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is a preview.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.51,0:52:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be hard to put faith\Nin something you cannot see.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.91,0:52:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But real faith is not blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.42,0:52:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Real faith is based on facts,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.55,0:52:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,on realities,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.53,0:53:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,on truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.73,0:53:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives us courage and strength,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.43,0:53:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and it helps us to endure.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.94,0:53:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When life gets hard, it provides peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.51,0:53:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It reminds us of our purpose,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.15,0:53:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and it brings us real joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.68,0:53:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn how to build and strengthen your faith
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.99,0:53:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,at the 2021 “Powerful by Faith!”\NConvention of Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.41,0:53:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it’s time for our video postcard,\Nwhich comes to us
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.41,0:53:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,from our brothers and sisters in Belarus.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.02,0:54:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Belarus is an Eastern European nation\Nthat borders Russia.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.22,0:54:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s known as
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.22,0:54:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the “blue-eyed” country\Nbecause it is dotted
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.23,0:54:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,with more than 10,000 lakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.36,0:54:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of Europe’s\Nmost ancient trees, as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.40,0:54:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,its largest mammal\N—the European bison—
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.34,0:54:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,can be found here.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.11,0:54:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Castles, some dating
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.51,0:54:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,from the 16th century, are popular sites.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.18,0:54:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Nesvizh Castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.99,0:54:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look up at the ceiling of its chapel,\Nyou’ll see Jehovah’s name
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.32,0:54:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in the form of the Tetragrammaton.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.09,0:54:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,When Belarus was part of the Soviet Union,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.10,0:54:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s Witnesses\Nfaced strong government opposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.57,0:54:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of our brothers\Nwere exiled to far-away Siberia.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.04,0:54:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, more than 6,000 publishers
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.01,0:55:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in 84 congregations\Nboldly declare the good news
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.45,0:55:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in Belarus.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.09,0:55:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a zealous pioneer spirit here.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.82,0:55:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Twenty percent of the publishers
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.36,0:55:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,are in full-time service.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.49,0:55:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how our brothers share the good news
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.53,0:55:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in the city of Brest.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.70,0:55:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They enjoy many aspects
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.00,0:55:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,of public witnessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.54,0:55:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are our brothers and sisters\Nin the city of Kobryn.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.41,0:55:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Their territory includes\Nboth urban and rural areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.05,0:55:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The 78 publishers here conduct an average
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.52,0:55:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of 74 Bible studies each month.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.66,0:55:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers and sisters in Belarus
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.89,0:55:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,send you their warm love and greetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.00,0:55:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Herman, it’s been a pleasure\Nreviewing this exciting material
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.10,0:55:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,about the “king of the north” with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.44,0:55:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Ken.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.87,0:56:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This information is so important.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.21,0:56:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It helps all of us
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.21,0:56:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to face the future with confidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.95,0:56:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Before we say goodbye,\Nwe have a treat for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.79,0:56:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s a preview of the video drama\Nfrom this year’s convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.42,0:56:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Please enjoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.88,0:56:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You will receive training
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.05,0:56:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in the house of the great King Nebuchadnezzar.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.75,0:56:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.68,0:56:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.12,0:56:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Be strong, my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.39,0:56:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a new land with new laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.73,0:56:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon they’ll want us to worship their gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.60,0:56:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is in Israel.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.07,0:57:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re in Babylon now.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.07,0:57:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s going to happen to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.35,0:57:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a dream,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.48,0:57:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and no one can tell him what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.91,0:57:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is to be executed by dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.62,0:57:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We have until morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.72,0:57:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,To do what?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.65,0:57:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.62,0:57:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They burned down Jehovah’s house!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.93,0:57:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as Jehovah exists,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.16,0:57:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we have hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.77,0:57:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Interpretations belong to my God, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.40,0:57:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows your dream and what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.97,0:57:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is your God?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.48,0:57:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill them!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.98,0:57:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,O Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.58,0:57:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,surely you didn’t bring us here to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.98,0:57:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, vindicate yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.29,0:58:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,As we’ve discussed in our program,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.10,0:58:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel played an important role\Nas Jehovah’s prophet.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.13,0:58:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we’ll see in our video drama,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.24,0:58:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s much we can learn\Nfrom his life and example.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.64,0:58:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, before we sign off,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.55,0:58:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a special musical gift video
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.71,0:58:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that closely relates\Nto our monthly program theme.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.59,0:58:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be encouraged and inspired.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.14,1:02:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Please keep our brothers\Nin Russia in your prayers.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.14,1:02:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn from their example\Nof faith and courage.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.78,1:02:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,See these events for what they are
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.38,1:02:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,—the fulfillment of Bible prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.79,1:02:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Let this knowledge\Nmove you to make wise decisions.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.19,1:03:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay faithful, and stay busy
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.26,1:03:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,as the end of this system draws close.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.40,1:03:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,From the World Headquarters\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.04,1:03:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,this is JW Broadcasting.
